claim.claim-text:
1. A photovoltaic cell comprising:
a substrate;
at least one first electrode electrically connected to said substrate;
at least two vertical walls disposed on said substrate, placed parallel to each other, such that a gap is formed between said at least two vertical walls,
wherein the at least two vertical walls are substantially perpendicular to the substrate;

an insulator layer disposed on the substrate between said at least two vertical walls;
at least one second electrode disposed on the insulator layer such that the insulator layer electrically isolates the at least one second electrode from the substrate as well as from the at least one first electrode;
at least one layer of electronic material disposed in said gap between said at least two vertical, walls, such that said insulator layer electrically isolates said at least one layer of electronic material from said substrate,
wherein said at least one layer of electronic material is as continuous layer, and;
at least one nanometer-scale rod, wire, or tube extending from first vertical wall of the at least two vertical walls to second vertical wall of the at least two vertical walls, such that said at least one nanometer-scale rod, wire, or tube bridges the gap between said at least two vertical walls,
wherein said at least one nanometer-scale rod, wire, or tube is embedded in said at least one layer of electronic material,
wherein junctions providing built-in electric field are formed at interfaces between the at least one nanometer-scale rod, wire, or tube and the at least one layer of electronic material surrounding the at Least one nanometer-scale rod, wire, or tube, and
wherein said junctions are ones selected from the group consisting of p-n junctions and Schottky junctions.

10. The photovoltaic cell of claim 1, wherein
the at least one first electrode is composed of a transparent conductive alloyed or non-alloyed metal;
the at least one nanometer-scale rod, wire, or tube is composed of GaN of n or p type; each of the at least one layer of electronic material electrically connected to the at least one first electrode is composed of p or n type InxGaxN, such that doping polarity is of the opposite kind from that in the at least one nanometer-scale rod, wire, or tube; and
the at least one second electrode is composed of a metal suitable to construct an ohmic contact to GaN;
wherein, for each layer of the at least one layer of electronic material, x is varied according to 0≦x≦1, such that a layer nearest to a surface receiving the incident electromagnetic radiation, has high Ga content resulting in a high band gap material, and a layer farthest from the surface has low Ga content resulting in a low band gap material.

12. A photovoltaic cell comprising:
a substrate;
at least one first electrode electrically connected to said substrate;
at least two vertical walls disposed on said substrate, placed parallel to each other, such that a gap is formed between the at least two vertical walls,
wherein the at least two vertical walls substantially perpendicular to the substrate;

an insulator layer disposed on the substrate between said at least two vertical walls;
at least one second electrode disposed on the insulator layer such that the insulator layer electrically isolates the at least one second electrode from the substrate as well as from the at least one first electrode;
at least one layer of electronic material disposed in said gap between said at least two vertical walls, such that said insulator layer electrically isolates said at least one layer of electronic material from said substrate,
wherein said at least one layer of electronic material is as continuous layer, and;

at least one nanometer-scale tube embedded in said at least one layer of electronic material, such that said at least one nanometer-scale tube bridges the gap between said vertical walls,
wherein junctions providing built-in electric field are formed at interfaces between the at least one nanometer-scale tube and the at least one layer of electronic material surrounding the at least one nanometer-scale tube, and wherein said junctions are ones selected from the group consisting of p-n junctions and Schottky junctions.

16. A photovoltaic cell, comprising:
a substrate;
at least one first electrode electrically connected said substrate;
at least two vertical walls disposed on said substrate, placed parallel to each other, such that a gap is formed between the at least two vertical walls,
wherein the at least two vertical walls are substantially perpendicular to the substrate;

an insulator layer disposed on the substrate between said at least two vertical walls;
at least one second electrode constructed on the insulator layer such that the insulator layer electrically isolates the at least one second electrode from the substrate as well as from the at least one first electrode;
at least one layer of electronic material disposed in said gap between said at least two vertical walls, such that said insulator layer electrically isolates said at least one layer of electronic material from said substrate,
wherein said at least one layer of electronic material is a continuous layer, and;

at least one nanometer-scale wire or rod embedded in said at least one layer of electronic material, such that said at least one nanometer-scale wire or rod bridges the gap between said at least two vertical walls,
wherein junctions providing built-in electric field are formed at interfaces between said at least one nanometer-scale wire or rod and the at least one layer electronic material surrounding the at least one nanometer-scale wire or rod, and
wherein said junctions are ones selected from the group consisting of p-n junctions and Schottky junctions.
